               pid=40,

               description="Set of meta definitions that form the extensions scheme. The meta definitions are the class definitions, property definitions and type definitions} that define extensions classes and properties for use in descriptive frameworks, descriptive objects, application plugin objects and application referenced objects.")
public Set<MetaDefinition> getMetaDefinitions()
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            throws PropertyNotPresentException
        Description copied from interface: ExtensionScheme

        Returns the set of meta definitions that form the extensions scheme. The meta definitions are the class definitions, property definitions and type definitions that define extensions classes and properties for use in:

        • descriptive frameworks;
        • descriptive objects;
        • application plugin objects;
        • application referenced objects.

        This is an optional property, although omitting it and defining an empty scheme would not make much sense.

        Specified by:
        getMetaDefinitions in interface ExtensionScheme
        Returns:
        Set of meta definitions that form the extensions scheme.
        Throws:
        PropertyNotPresentException - The optional meta definitions property is not present for this extension scheme.
